===Noun===
'''jiffy''' (''plural'' '''[[jiffies]]''')

# {{colloquial}} A very short, unspecified length of time.
#:''I'll be back in a jiffy.''
# (''computers'') A unit of time defined by the frequency of the OS timing system; for x86-class hardware, this periodic tick initially had a period of 10ms. As average system speed increased, this was changed for some architectures to 1ms, and recently corrected to 4ms (the Linux 2.6 kernel timing subsystem implements an adjustable timing parameter that sets the jiffy time between 1ms and 10ms).
# {{physics}} The time taken for light to travel one centimetre in a vacuum (sometimes one foot, or sometimes the width of a [[nucleon]])
# {{electronics}} The time between [[alternating current]] power cycles (1/60 or 1/50 of a second)

